from flask import Flask, request, render_template
import requests

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/', methods=['GET', 'POST'])
def index():
    if request.method == 'POST':
        location = request.form.get('location')
        radius = request.form.get('radius')
        url = f'https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/place/nearbysearch/json'
        params = {
            'location': location,
            'radius': radius,
            'type': 'restaurant',
            'key': 'YOUR_API_KEY'
        }
        response = requests.get(url, params=params).json()
        restaurants = response['results']
        return render_template('index.html', restaurants=restaurants)
    return render_template('index.html')

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run()
```

This application uses the Flask web framework and the Google Places API to fetch nearby restaurants for a given location and radius. Users can input their current location and desired search radius, and the application will display a list of restaurants in the specified area.

To use this application, you will need to replace 'YOUR_API_KEY' with a valid API key from the Google Cloud Console. Additionally, you may wish to customize the HTML templates used to display the restaurant data to the user.
